<SECOND>PM-Thailand-Crash,0103</SECOND>
<HEAD>16 Killed, 30 Injured in Bus Crash</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sixteen people were killed and 30
injured when a local tourist bus and a truck collided in
southeastern Thailand, police said today.
   Police Lt. Rathsith Doungngung said the accident occurred
Thursday near Chanthaburi, about 130 miles southeast of the capital
Bangkok. Rathsith said both the bus and truck drivers fled the scene
of the accident.
   The crash was the second accident involving a tourist bus in
Thailand this month. On June 7, 22 people were killed when a tour
bus was struck by a truck in central Thailand.
