<HEAD>Hong Kong Announces Moratorium On Ivory Imports</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HONG KONG (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The government today announced a moratorium on
imports of raw ivory in an effort to protect the African elephant.
   A government statement said that until further notice, the
Agriculture and Fisheries Department will stop processing of
applications for licences to import raw ivory.
   The moratorium is applicable to all ivory traders and importers,
except those who had entered into contractual obligation for the
purchase of raw ivory before today's announcement.
