<SECOND>PM-France-Reagan,0145</SECOND>
<HEAD>Reagan Meets French Premier Rocard</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PARIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Former President Reagan met with Premier Michel
Rocard today and discussed events in China and the Soviet Union,
French officials said.
   Reagan and Rocard strolled around the gardens of the premier's
residence, the Hotel Matignon and talked for 40 minutes. The topics
included disarmament and the China's crackdown on the student-led
pro-democracy movement in China, officials in Rocard's office said
on condition of anonymity.
   Rocard showed Reagan a mural inscribed with the 1789 Declaration
of the Rights of Man, which now decorates a walls at the Matignon.
   On Thursday, the first day of his visit, Reagan was made an
associate member of the French Academy of Moral and Political
Sciences.
   Before he returns home, Reagan is to participate in festivities
Saturday night marking the 100th anniversary of the Eiffel Tower.
