   An engineer inspecting a Pakistan
International Airlines plane after an emergency landing was crushed
to death when the nose gear collapsed, officials said Friday.
   The twin-engine Fokker 27 had landed safely on a flight from
Bahawalpur on Thursday with about 30 passengers and crew after the
pilot alerted Sukkur airport that instruments showed his nose gear
