<HEAD>Bush Declares Federal Disaster Status for Louisiana</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush on Friday declared federal
disaster status for the state of Louisiana as a result of major
storms and tornadoes that hit the southern part of the state last
week.
   Included in the disaster declaration were the parishes of East
and West Baton Rouge, Iberville, Livingston, St. Helena and Vernon.
   The Federal Emergency Management Agency is continuing to review
the damage and include some other affected parishes, the White House
said.
   Federal disaster status allows for federal aid, including
temporary housing and grants to affected individuals, and loans to
businesses.
