<FIRST>r a AM-HeavyChoice     06-16 0238</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Heavy Choice,0243</SECOND>
<HEAD>Judge: Lose Weight or Go to Jail</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JIM THORPE, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 311{-pound man who hasn't made child
support payments for more than a year because he's too overweight to
work is under court order to lose 50 pounds or go to jail.
   Charles Petro has gained 85 pounds in the year since his doctor
told the Carbon County Court that obesity was making his patient's
back condition worse.
   Common Pleas Court President Judge John P. Lavelle found Petro in
contempt of court on June 9 because Petro had gained the weight in
the year since he first went before the judge for the same reason.
   ``I call it my `Oprah Winfrey sentence,''' Lavelle said Thursday.
``It's designed to make him lose weight for the benefit of his
children, while Oprah lost weight for the benefit of her job and
future security.''
   Lavelle set Sept. 9 as the deadline for Petro to shed 50 pounds
or go to jail for 90 days. To verify Petro's weight, the judge sent
him to a nearby medical center where he was weighed.
   ``I said to him, `No sacrifice should be too much for a man who
has a duty to support his children,'' Lavelle said. ``The only way
this man will ever get back to being a productive worker is if he
loses weight.''
   Petro, who has two children, could not be reached Friday for
comment.
</TEXT>
