<SECOND>PM-Shearson,0159</SECOND>
<HEAD>Shearson Agrees To Sell Money Management Unit</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Shearson Lehman Hutton Holdings Inc. said it has
agreed to sell the institutional money management businesses of
Lehman Management Co. Inc. to a management-led group for $100
million in cash.
   Under the transaction, announced Thursday, Shearson will buy a
20-percent equity stake valued at $9 million from Lehman-ARK
Acquisition Inc., the newly formed corporation of Lehman Management
executives.
   Shearson, a New York-based securities and investment banking
concern, said owning stock in the new company would allow it to
participate in the future growth and profitability of the business,
which will be operated as Lehman-ARK Management Co.
   Shearson said it would retain Lehman Management's mutual fund,
equity management and individual investor services business.
   The sale is subject to approval by Shearson's board and
regulatory authorities.
   Shearson's principal subsidiary is Shearson Lehman Hutton Inc., a
registered broker dealer.
