<FIRST>r f PM-AutoRecall     06-16 0103</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Auto Recall,0107</SECOND>
<HEAD>Honda Recalls 77,000 '88 Preludes</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   American Honda Motor Co. Inc. has recalled about
77,000 1988 Prelude automobiles to eliminate potential accelerator
pedal and front-seat problems.
   The company said in a news release received Thursday that rubber
blocks would be installed under accelerator pedals in all 77,000
Preludes. Under extreme pressure, the pedal could be caught by a
stopper covered by floor material.
   Also, the company said it would reinforce front-seat anchors that
don't meet federal strength specifications in about 25,000 of the
cars. All work would be done at no cost to the consumer, Honda said.
</TEXT>
